Now we define the Wigner space, measure, and matrix map.
The Wigner space is the index set `Index n` (lower triangular indices) mapped to real numbers.
The Wigner measure is the product measure of `μ` and `ν` over the index set.
The Wigner matrix map `wignerMatrixMap` creates a matrix from the Wigner space element.
The scaled Wigner matrix map `wignerMatrixMapScaled` creates a scaled matrix.

```tactics
/-/

