The map `wignerMatrixMap'` is `Matrix.of (wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω)`. Since `wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω` is a function from `Fin n` to `ℝ`, `Matrix.of` applied to it is a map from `Fin n` to `Fin n` to `ℝ`, which is a matrix. The function `wignerMatrixMap'` is therefore a map from `WignerSpace n` to `Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ`. 

To prove that `wignerMatrixMap'` is measurable, we need to show that for any matrix entry `(i, j)`, the function `ω ↦ (wignerMatrixMap' ω) i j` is measurable. 

