This is still not simple enough. Let's use the fact that `wignerMatrixMap'` is a map from `WignerSpace n` to `Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ`. The function `wignerMatrixMap'` is `Matrix.of (wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω)`. 

The function `wignerMatrixEntryFunction` is a function from `WignerSpace n` to `ℝ`. For fixed `i, j`, the value `(wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω) i j` is `ω p` for some `p : Fin n × Fin n` such that `p.val.1 ≤ p.val.2`. 

The function `ω ↦ ω p` is measurable. Therefore, all entries of the matrix `wignerMatrixMap' ω` are measurable functions of `ω`. Therefore, `wignerMatrixMap'` is a measurable map.

